<section class="material-faq">

  <div class="container">

    <h2>
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </h2>

    <p class="section-intro">
      Common questions about Calacatta Viola marble and custom stone fabrication.
    </p>

    <div class="faq-list">

      <details class="faq-item">

        <summary>
          Is every Calacatta Viola slab identical?
        </summary>

        <p>
          No. Calacatta Viola is a natural marble, and every slab features unique veining, color movement and pattern distribution.
        </p>

      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">

        <summary>
          Can Calacatta Viola be used in bathrooms?
        </summary>

        <p>
          Yes. It is widely used for vanity tops, sinks, wall cladding and luxury bathroom applications.
        </p>

      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">

        <summary>
          What finishes are available?
        </summary>

        <p>
          Common finishes include polished, honed, leathered and brushed surfaces depending on the project requirements.
        </p>

      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">

        <summary>
          Can you fabricate custom products from this material?
        </summary>

        <p>
          Yes. We can fabricate custom sinks, tables, bathtubs, furniture and architectural elements using Calacatta Viola marble.
        </p>

      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">

        <summary>
          Are alternative materials available?
        </summary>

        <p>
          Yes. Similar visual styles may be achieved with Bianca Calacatta, Panda White, Volakas White and other premium marbles.
        </p>

      </details>

    </div>

  </div>

</section>

